    "overview": "Operative details regarding Which is the largest river... under the category of Pakistan History.",
    "question": "Which is the largest river among Ravi, Chenab and Sutlej? The Chenab River is the largest among the three rivers in water flow and significance within Pakistan. It has a total length of 974 km (605 miles), with 730.6 km flowing through Pakistan. Its water flow of 977.3 cubic meters per second is the highest among the three, making it an essential source of water for irrigation, hydroelectric power, and agriculture. Originating in Himachal Pradesh, India, It enters Pakistan and serves as a primary water resource under the Indus Waters Treaty. Due to its consistent water supply and vast basin area, it plays a crucial role in Pakistan's river system. The Sutlej River is the longest in total length, spanning 1,450 km (900 miles), but only 530.6 km of it lies within Pakistan. Much of its water is diverted in India for irrigation and hydroelectric projects, leading to a significant reduction in its flow within Pakistan. While it is the longest overall, its contribution to Pakistan's river system is minimal due to water diversions. The Ravi River is the smallest among the three, with a total length of 725 km (450 miles), of which 680.6 km lies within Pakistan. It has the lowest water flow, as most of its water is withheld in India, significantly reducing its availability for irrigation and consumption. While Sutlej is the longest in total length, Chenab has the longest stretch within Pakistan and carries the highest volume of water. It is also the most important river for Pakistan's irrigation system. Final Answer: (B) Chenab - the largest based on water volume, longest stretch within Pakistan, and overall importance in Pakistan's hydrological system.",
