    "question": "A milkman adds 10 litre water in 10 litre milk. His son takes 15 litre of the milk and adds 5 litre water in it. Find out the amount of water in litres in this milk? Mixture of milk and water = 10l + 10 liters = 20 liters ⇒ So, milk water ratio is 1:1 ⇒ Son takes 15 liters of mixture i.e. 7.5 liter milk +7.5 liter water ⇒ Water = 7.5 liter ⇒ After adding 5 liter of water = 7.5 + 5 Total water = 12.5 liter",
