    "question": "X^2 > y^2 then possible solution is: (X is greater than Y) Since X^2 > Y^2, we can take the square root of both sides: √(X^2) > √ This simplifies to: |X| > |Y| Since the absolute value of X is greater than the absolute value of Y, we can conclude that X is greater than Y. Note that this assumes that X and Y are real numbers. If X and Y are complex numbers, the situation is more complicated, and the conclusion might not hold. So, the correct answer is (A) X is greater than Y.",
