    "context": "Diagnostic Instruments: Stethoscope: Used to listen to internal body sounds such as the heartbeat, lung sounds, and bowel movements. (Helps detect abnormalities like murmurs, arrhythmias, or respiratory issues) Thermometer: Measures body temperature. (Helps identify fever, hypothermia, or infections) Sphygmomanometer: Measures blood pressure. (Helps diagnose hypertension, hypotension, or cardiovascular conditions) Otoscope: Used to examine the ear canal and eardrum. (Detects ear infections, blockages, or perforations in the eardrum) Ophthalmoscope: Used to examine the interior of the eye, including the retina and optic nerve. (Helps diagnose conditions like glaucoma, diabetic retinopathy, or retinal detachment) Pulse Oximeter: Measures oxygen saturation levels in the blood and pulse rate. (Monitors respiratory or cardiac issues, such as hypoxemia or pneumonia) Electrocardiogram (ECG or EKG) Machine: Records the electrical activity of the heart. (Diagnoses arrhythmias, heart attacks, or other cardiac abnormalities) Endoscope: A flexible or rigid tube with a camera used to view internal organs or cavities. (Identifies conditions like ulcers, tumors, or blockages in the gastrointestinal tract) Ultrasound Machine: Uses sound waves to create images of internal organs and tissues. (Monitors pregnancies, detects organ abnormalities, or guides biopsies) MRI (Magnetic Resonance Imaging) Scanner: Uses magnetic fields and radio waves to produce detailed images of soft tissues. (Diagnoses brain tumors, joint problems, or spinal cord injuries) X-Ray Machine: Uses radiation to produce images of bones and certain tissues. (Detects fractures, infections, or lung conditions like pneumonia) CT (Computed Tomography) Scanner: Creates cross- sectional images of the body using X-rays. (Diagnoses cancers, internal injuries, or blood clots) Mammography Machine: Specialized X-ray for breast imaging. (Detects early signs of breast cancer or other abnormalities) Glucometer: Measures blood glucose levels. (Monitors diabetes and helps manage blood sugar levels) Laryngoscope: Used to view the larynx and vocal cords. (Commonly used during intubation or to diagnose throat conditions) Colposcope: Magnifies and illuminates the cervix and vagina for examination. (Detects cervical abnormalities and guides biopsies) Tuning Fork: Produces vibrations to assess hearing or detect nerve damage. (Used in hearing tests or to diagnose fractures) Spirometer: Measures lung capacity and airflow. (Diagnoses conditions like asthma or COPD) Dermatoscope: Magnifies the skin for detailed examination. (Identifies skin lesions, moles, and early signs of skin cancer)",
